ply the\n$(p,k)$ parametrization of the Eisenstein series $E_4(\\tau)$ and its\nduplications. It is to be noted that the $(p,k)$ parametrization of $E_4$ and\nits duplications were derived by a different method by K. S. Williams and his\nco-authors. In the final section, we provide sample formulas for these\nrepresentation numbers in the case of 4 and 6 variable forms.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 12 Apr 2019 18:27:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 1 May 2019 08:04:59 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 22 Jun 2019 19:12:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-25"}
